Example for running the script remotely (from http://stackoverflow.com/questions/305035/how-to-use-ssh-to-run-shell-script-on-a-remote-machine):

```
ssh root@MachineB 'bash -s' < local_script.sh
```

Note: ssh on localhost without password.  See: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/7439563/hard-how-to-ssh-localhost-without-password
